<Content>Valiant Attempt At Mediocrity To begin with, Guayanilla is in the middle of nowhere  is not a tourist destination; I used it as a stopover during an 8-day circumnavigation of the island. The pool was not in working order  there was massive construction going on right outside the property (they are adding a casino). The one bright spot was the restaurant which is a Meson Gastronomico  has certainly earned that certification. The property might fare better scrapping the hotel  just running the restaurant  bar. However, if it's good enough for Miss Puerto Rico to stay there (as she was during my trip)... I guess her standards are lower than mine. 
