<Content>Not ready for prime time My wife and I planned to stay here two nights in April, but left after the first night.Nothing went right for us here, starting when we were searching to find the place. I don't remember the details, but the address is listed as being on a numbered route. Five miles north of town we eventually admitted that we'd missed it. We came back and searched... and searched... and eventually had to call for directions. (Thank you Sprint for 'home area' coverage in PR !)The room was tiny and cramped. A huge entertainment center only took up needless space and mocked the small TV inside. There was only space for a nightstand on one side of the bed.Part of our bad experience was due to timing. The road out in front was under construction, and it felt like it would rip out the suspension of our car every time we came and went. The pool was closed for major repairs. All in all I felt like I was trapped in a tiny cell with no place to go and nothing to do but stare at the walls.On the plus side, the staff was as friendly as they could be. 
