<Content>Great value, location First review, and it's very good! This very clean and well-maintained parador provides great value for the money. Location was especially appreciated: it's outside the traffic congestion of Ponce, but close enough (15 minutes to parking in historic Ponce) to enjoy sightseeing, dining, etc. It's also on the west side of Ponce, providing a convenient getaway to La Parguera's luminescent lagoon and the whole southwest and west of Puerto Rico. I arrived late at night, called via cell phone for directions from Ponce, and was dreading the usual sleepy, semi-incoherent mumbles from a night clerk. However, I was quite welcomed, and obtained clear, simple directions. It turns out I didn't even need them, as this parador is very clearly signed from Hwy 2. I *highly* recommend this place! They are expanding, and deservedly so. 
